2.9 The Future of Cthugha for Linux
===================================

Some plans I have with Cthugha for Linux:

   * Make it more independent from Linux. I think `xcthugha' should run
     on every unix system fast enough at least when using just random
     data or a sound file as input.

   * Cut it down a little bit. This has already started. Screen saver
     and DGA support are no longer included. More things might follow.
     The whole thing is just getting too big for me. I will remove
     parts for which good alternatives exist or which are useless.

   * `svgalib'. To me it seems, that this library is slowly dying.
     Newer chips are not longer supported. So in the future I will
     probably only continue on the X11 version.

   * User interface. The current user interface is not really good -
     here are some changes necessary.

   * Copying Policy. This is definitely not change. I will never charge
     you for private use. I think about putting the whole thing under
     the GNU public license.

   * GGI. Maybe I combine X, svgalib and OpenGL version into just one
     program using GGI. This should also work with linux-fb.



